name='''We can access the real part and imaginary part separately using dot operator.\n1.real property of the complex number returns real part.\n2.imag property of the complex number returns imaginary part.\nIn the following example, we shall initialize a complex number and print real and image parts separately.\nPython Program:'''
cn=complex(5,6)
print('Real part is:',cn.real)
print('Imaginary part is:',cn.imag)